reviewText: A show for young children, fun to watch the boy and his dog get one over on the crooks and stop the bad guys from getting the treasure. Very funny and entertaining. My son watches it repeatedly, re-watching the bad guys getting theirs over and over again.
Title: Dog Gone

reviewText: “DOG GONE” (2008) - PG  107 minutes“Dog Gone” is basically, “Home Alone” in the woods. When 12 year old Owen rescues a dog from three men abusing the dog at a highway rest stop, he has no idea that the three are bumbling jewel thieves and that the dog is carrying five million dollars worth of stolen diamonds. Owen takes the dog back to his secret fort, high on a wooded ridge, a ridge that is also home to the “Madman of the Mountain.”  With a deadline approaching, the three jewel thieves search for Owen and finally grab him at his house. But Owen escapes back to his fort, which he has rigged with ingenious booby-traps and a wicked tennis-ball cannon named the “Bully Buster.”  The three dumb-as-rocks thieves, played with gusto by French Stewart, Kevin Farley and Kelly Perine, follow Owen to a final show-down.  After a hilarious battle, Owen and the dog, who Owen has named Diamond, are captured again. But Owen has unseen allies in two squirrels named Blabbermouth and Chatterbox and the mysterious, Madman on the Mountain.  In the end, the three jewel thieves wish they’d never been born. “Dog Gone” delivers all the hilarious and good-natured comedy that a classic family film should.
summary: Home Alone Goes Hilariously To The Dogs
Title: Dog Gone

reviewText: Anybody that likes dog stories or movies like Home Alone will like this one.  It has a good story line with a sweet lovable dog that is being used to smuggle diamonds when a kid with a big heart steps in to help her and put away the diamond smugglers.  Add in another kindred spirit that adds a lending hand and you get a feel good ending.
Title: Dog Gone
